title: The Jeff Healey Band - House of Blues Chicago(Deluxe 2-CD)
description:
The Jeff Healey Band - House of Blues Chicago(Deluxe 2-CD) 2018 ak320

Healey began playing guitar when he was three, developing his unique style of playing the instrument flat on his lap. At age 9 his musical talents were showcased in an interview on the TVOntario children's programme Cucumber. When he was 15, Jeff Healey formed the band Blue Direction, a four-piece which primarily played bar-band cover tunes. And it was on... 

Later...

A perfect soundboard recording, and a great performance! Of note here, Healey's rendition of Neil Young's "Like a Hurricaine", recorded for his "Cover to Cover" album but not included on that collection. Electric sets bookmark an all too short acoustic set that features a rendition of the blues classic "Outskirts of Town". Dan Akroyd guests on Arthur Crudrup's "Dig Myself a Hole" at the encore. A fun show! 
And other Bonus tracks only in this analogkid share. Why? Cause I love the music and it's what I do.
